summary: This is a business record certification from Municipal Credit Union in response to a subpoena duces tecum, certifying the accuracy and completeness of records produced. It indicates that checks and credit card statements were not applicable to the subpoena and that SARs/CTRs would be handled separately.

persons.name: Danielle Jones
persons.context: She is a duly authorized custodian of records for Municipal Credit Union who certifies the accuracy and completeness of documents produced in response to a subpoena.

persons.name: Patricia Gonzalez
persons.context: She is a notary public who notarized the certification document, qualified in Queens County, New York.

events.title: Business Record Certification Submission
events.description: Municipal Credit Union, through custodian Danielle Jones, certifies records in response to a subpoena duces tecum, indicating checks and credit card statements were not applicable.

keyFacts: Municipal Credit Union responded to a subpoena duces tecum with certified business records.
The certification states that checks and credit card statements were 'Not Applicable' to the subpoena request.
Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs) and Currency Transaction Reports (CTRs) were not included in this production and would be handled separately by the BSA Department.
